-- Ex-Goldman, Noble trader's new hedge fund gains 11 pct in Sept.
-- By Nishant Kumar
-- Tue Oct 14, 2014 03:33AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Oct 14 (Reuters) - Guard Capital, a macro hedge fund firm launched by two former top traders at Goldman Sachs <GS.N> and Noble Group in August, gained 11.2 percent last month as its currency and interest rate bets paid off, a letter to investors obtained by Reuters showed.

The Guard Macro Master Fund, which bets mainly on the currency and interest rate markets, outperformed a 1.8 percent gain in the HFRI Macro Index in September.